In order to analyze the problem, I need to know what arguments that chpass
was called with.   Please pkg_delete the port, remove the msql user from
your passwd file, and apply the following patch to
ports/databases/msql/scripts/createuser:

--- createuser.orig	Tue Mar 30 12:11:15 1999
+++ createuser	Tue Mar 30 12:13:21 1999
@@ -32,7 +32,9 @@
 print "msql user using uid $msqlUID\n";
 print "msql user using gid $msqlGID\n";

-system( "/usr/bin/chpass -a \"msql:*:$msqlUID:$msqlGID::0:0:mSQL-2 pseudo-user:/var/db/msqldb:/bin/sh\"" );
+$chpassargs = "\"msql:*:$msqlUID:$msqlGID::0:0:mSQL-2 pseudo-user:/var/db/msqldb:/bin/sh\"";
+system( "logger args to chpass are $chpassargs" );
+system( "/usr/bin/chpass -a $chpassargs" );

 sub append_file {
 	local($file,@list) = @_;


Then, re-install the port.  The arguments that are passed to chpass should
show up in your syslog (probably /var/log/messages if your haven't changed
syslog.conf from the default).  Please submit a followup to the PR once you
have this info and I'll see if I can fix the problem.

